data.description: Step into 316 W Oppenheimer, a charming home that lives up to its aesthetic appeal. Upon entering, you'll be welcomed by the warmth of hardwood flooring and well-designed lighting in the living room. One of the bedrooms boasts new flooring, having shed its previous carpet to reveal the natural beauty of hardwood floors throughout. The garage has undergone a transformation, now fully insulated with added windows. The removal of garage doors has turned this space into a versatile enclosed area, perfect for a game room or additional living space. With 3 bedrooms and 1 bath, this home offers a comfortable and spacious layout, complemented by a generous kitchen and a well-appointed laundry room. Situated on a corner lot at the intersection of Grove and Oppenheimer St, the property features a chain-linked fenced backyard. Lush oak trees scattered throughout create a picturesque oasis. Ample parking is available both in front and on the side. This cute and charming home is not just a residence but a delightful retreat for those seeking a perfect blend of comfort and aesthetics.
